.org/the-events-calendar/assets/screenshot-4.png?rev=1679210\"><img src=\"https://ps.w.org/the-events-calendar/assets/screenshot-4.png?rev=1679210\" alt=\"Vista diaria\"></a><p>Vista diaria</p></li><li><a href=\"https://ps.w.org/the-events-calendar/assets/screenshot-5.png?rev=1679210\"><img src=\"https://ps.w.org/the-events-calendar/assets/screenshot-5.png?rev=1679210\" alt=\"Single event\"></a><p>Single event</p></li><li><a href=\"https://ps.w.org/the-events-calendar/assets/screenshot-6.png?rev=1679210\"><img src=\"https://ps.w.org/the-events-calendar/assets/screenshot-6.png?rev=1679210\" alt=\"Event Editor\"></a><p>Event Editor</p></li><li><a href=\"https://ps.w.org/the-events-calendar/assets/screenshot-7.png?rev=1679210\"><img src=\"https://ps.w.org/the-events-calendar/assets/screenshot-7.png?rev=1679210\" alt=\"Events admin listing\"></a><p>Events admin listing</p></li><li><a href=\"https://ps.w.org/the-events-calendar/assets/screenshot-8.png?rev=1679210\"><img src=\"https://ps.w.org/the-events-calendar/assets/screenshot-8.png?rev=1679210\" alt=\"Ajustes generales\"></a><p>Ajustes generales</p></li><li><a href=\"https://ps.w.org/the-events-calendar/assets/screenshot-9.png?rev=1679210\"><img src=\"https://ps.w.org/the-events-calendar/assets/screenshot-9.png?rev=1679210\" alt=\"Ajustes de visualización\"></a><p>Ajustes de visualización</p></li></ol>\";s:7:\"reviews\";s:15131:\"<div class=\"review\">\n	<div class=\"review-head\">\n		<div class=\"reviewer-info\">\n			<div class=\"review-title-section\">\n				<h4 class=\"review-title\">bad coding</h4>\n				<div class=\"star-rating\">\n				<div class=\"wporg-ratings\" aria-label=\"1 de 5 estrellas\" data-title-template=\"%s de 5 estrellas\" data-rating=\"1\" style=\"color:#ffb900;\"><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span></div>				</div>\n			</div>\n			<p class=\"reviewer\">\n				Por <a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/chicho1969\"><img alt=\'\' src=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/4c91fec0ac6881ffaf274f0e5093f767?s=16&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g\' srcset=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/4c91fec0ac6881ffaf274f0e5093f767?s=32&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g 2x\' class=\'avatar avatar-16 photo\' height=\'16\' width=\'16\' /></a><a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/chicho1969\" class=\"reviewer-name\">chicho1969</a> el <span class=\"review-date\">April 17, 2019</span>			</p>\n		</div>\n	</div>\n	<div class=\"review-body\">changing events or event slug result in 404 page, this issue still from 2015 up today. Slugs are not clear and documentation is worst.  cannot change slug. Do not understand and do not find an explanation for slugs event, events, tc-events...</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"review\">\n	<div class=\"review-head\">\n		<div class=\"reviewer-info\">\n			<div class=\"review-title-section\">\n				<h4 class=\"review-title\">WOW - Best Rendering Calendar Plugin</h4>\n				<div class=\"star-rating\">\n				<div class=\"wporg-ratings\" aria-label=\"5 de 5 estrellas\" data-title-template=\"%s de 5 estrellas\" data-rating=\"5\" style=\"color:#ffb900;\"><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span></div>				</div>\n			</div>\n			<p class=\"reviewer\">\n				Por <a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/kdawg1406\"><img alt=\'\' src=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/e62fc1a875bfaac4f1241bdded4b0f7f?s=16&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g\' srcset=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/e62fc1a875bfaac4f1241bdded4b0f7f?s=32&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g 2x\' class=\'avatar avatar-16 photo\' height=\'16\' width=\'16\' /></a><a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/kdawg1406\" class=\"reviewer-name\">kdawg1406</a> el <span class=\"review-date\">April 11, 2019</span>			</p>\n		</div>\n	</div>\n	<div class=\"review-body\">I\'ve spent the last three weeks looking for a Calendar that had these features:\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Works with dark WordPress theme</li>\n	<li>Ability to perform design-time filtering or server-side filtering</li>\n	<li>Renders outstanding on mobile or desktop</li>\n	<li>Easy for average person to enter events </li>\n	<li>Good documentation</li>\n	<li>Responsive support - community or vendor</li>\n</ul>\n\nAfter downloading and testing or purchasing and testing many calendars I finally found The Events Calendar late last night.\n\nWOW - this events calendar is outstanding.  The rendering of the templates is by far the best I\'ve seen, especially how they render images.  No overstretching or strange image rending.  You upload the image, that is how it looks on the single page view.\n\nWhile this plugin does not work with Elementor Pro as an editor, you can download a plugin to enable the use of shortcodes on any page.\n\nOne issue I ran into was it can be difficult to wade through their docs because, they have other products, one called Community Events, which is a different product, when searching on the web you have to deal with Community Events results when you only want content for this calendar.\n\nGreat job, love this calendar, thank you so very much,\n\nKarl\n\n\n\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"review\">\n	<div class=\"review-head\">\n		<div class=\"reviewer-info\">\n			<div class=\"review-title-section\">\n				<h4 class=\"review-title\">Few problems</h4>\n				<div class=\"star-rating\">\n				<div class=\"wporg-ratings\" aria-label=\"2 de 5 estrellas\" data-title-template=\"%s de 5 estrellas\" data-rating=\"2\" style=\"color:#ffb900;\"><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span></div>				</div>\n			</div>\n			<p class=\"reviewer\">\n				Por <a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/ridelikeagirlproject\"><img alt=\'\' src=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/430c453766d25421eb554a71b83bd0e9?s=16&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g\' srcset=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/430c453766d25421eb554a71b83bd0e9?s=32&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g 2x\' class=\'avatar avatar-16 photo\' height=\'16\' width=\'16\' /></a><a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/ridelikeagirlproject\" class=\"reviewer-name\">ridelikeagirlproject</a> el <span class=\"review-date\">April 9, 2019</span>			</p>\n		</div>\n	</div>\n	<div class=\"review-body\">The widget is good and I like it but unfortunately I\'m having few problems with the event layout and now <strong>I also can\'t create any new events and I see in Profile\'s column Disable</strong>.\n\nHope I can solve this otherwise I have quickly change plugin.</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"review\">\n	<div class=\"review-head\">\n		<div class=\"reviewer-info\">\n			<div class=\"review-title-section\">\n				<h4 class=\"review-title\">Lends a professional look</h4>\n				<div class=\"star-rating\">\n				<div class=\"wporg-ratings\" aria-label=\"5 de 5 estrellas\" data-title-template=\"%s de 5 estrellas\" data-rating=\"5\" style=\"color:#ffb900;\"><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span></div>				</div>\n			</div>\n			<p class=\"reviewer\">\n				Por <a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/ereihl\"><img alt=\'\' src=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/4314ed6dc454f0771d864dfd5310d04f?s=16&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g\' srcset=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/4314ed6dc454f0771d864dfd5310d04f?s=32&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g 2x\' class=\'avatar avatar-16 photo\' height=\'16\' width=\'16\' /></a><a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/ereihl\" class=\"reviewer-name\">ereihl</a> el <span class=\"review-date\">April 1, 2019</span>			</p>\n		</div>\n	</div>\n	<div class=\"review-body\">I really like the appearance of the calendar. It looks professional and the UI is very intuitive. I am currently using it for a training portal site.</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"review\">\n	<div class=\"review-head\">\n		<div class=\"reviewer-info\">\n			<div class=\"review-title-section\">\n				<h4 class=\"review-title\">This does the job nicely...</h4>\n				<div class=\"star-rating\">\n				<div class=\"wporg-ratings\" aria-label=\"5 de 5 estrellas\" data-title-template=\"%s de 5 estrellas\" data-rating=\"5\" style=\"color:#ffb900;\"><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span></div>				</div>\n			</div>\n			<p class=\"reviewer\">\n				Por <a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/crzyhrse\"><img alt=\'\' src=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/c92f6fbad5b684dd17d1fde21aff8c24?s=16&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g\' srcset=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/c92f6fbad5b684dd17d1fde21aff8c24?s=32&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g 2x\' class=\'avatar avatar-16 photo\' height=\'16\' width=\'16\' /></a><a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/crzyhrse\" class=\"reviewer-name\">crzyhrse</a> el <span class=\"review-date\">March 27, 2019</span>			</p>\n		</div>\n	</div>\n	<div class=\"review-body\">I have had to spend a lot of time learning the plugin so I could change its appearance and some of the ways it works, but it is doing great now...\n\nAll in all thanks for all the work that has been done on this plugin. for… I need to use the free version because both sites are two different non-profit community oriented situations….  No income from the sites... </div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"review\">\n	<div class=\"review-head\">\n		<div class=\"reviewer-info\">\n			<div class=\"review-title-section\">\n				<h4 class=\"review-title\">Not usable</h4>\n				<div class=\"star-rating\">\n				<div class=\"wporg-ratings\" aria-label=\"5 de 5 estrellas\" data-title-template=\"%s de 5 estrellas\" data-rating=\"5\" style=\"color:#ffb900;\"><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span></div>				</div>\n			</div>\n			<p class=\"reviewer\">\n				Por <a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/lucge\"><img alt=\'\' src=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/fa479e1aef811420bd2be8ec125ba710?s=16&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g\' srcset=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/fa479e1aef811420bd2be8ec125ba710?s=32&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g 2x\' class=\'avatar avatar-16 photo\' height=\'16\' width=\'16\' /></a><a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/lucge\" class=\"reviewer-name\">lucge</a> el <span class=\"review-date\">March 23, 2019</span>			</p>\n		</div>\n	</div>\n	<div class=\"review-body\">The plugin does not recognize locations already in the database. </div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"review\">\n	<div class=\"review-head\">\n		<div class=\"reviewer-info\">\n			<div class=\"review-title-section\">\n				<h4 class=\"review-title\">Displaying past dates only</h4>\n				<div class=\"star-rating\">\n				<div class=\"wporg-ratings\" aria-label=\"1 de 5 estrellas\" data-title-template=\"%s de 5 estrellas\" data-rating=\"1\" style=\"color:#ffb900;\"><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span></div>				</div>\n			</div>\n			<p class=\"reviewer\">\n				Por <a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/littledove22\"><img alt=\'\' src=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/ee08172df3fdcadfbd7927678637d1b5?s=16&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g\' srcset=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/ee08172df3fdcadfbd7927678637d1b5?s=32&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g 2x\' class=\'avatar avatar-16 photo\' height=\'16\' width=\'16\' /></a><a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/littledove22\" class=\"reviewer-name\">littledove22</a> el <span class=\"review-date\">March 17, 2019</span>			</p>\n		</div>\n	</div>\n	<div class=\"review-body\">What is the use of displaying past dates?  The plugin does not display Scheduled Dates.\n\"The Events Calendar Shortcode &amp; Block\" plugin does nothing.  Even with the shortcode plugin disabled, only past shows display.  \n\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"review\">\n	<div class=\"review-head\">\n		<div class=\"reviewer-info\">\n			<div class=\"review-title-section\">\n				<h4 class=\"review-title\">ugly</h4>\n				<div class=\"star-rating\">\n				<div class=\"wporg-ratings\" aria-label=\"1 de 5 estrellas\" data-title-template=\"%s de 5 estrellas\" data-rating=\"1\" style=\"color:#ffb900;\"><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span></div>				</div>\n			</div>\n			<p class=\"reviewer\">\n				Por <a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/laset\"><img alt=\'\' src=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/539a600a19d3a6e5170f1302ef80e4f4?s=16&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g\' srcset=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/539a600a19d3a6e5170f1302ef80e4f4?s=32&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g 2x\' class=\'avatar avatar-16 photo\' height=\'16\' width=\'16\' /></a><a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/laset\" class=\"reviewer-name\">Laset <small>(LaSet)</small></a> el <span class=\"review-date\">March 15, 2019</span>			</p>\n		</div>\n	</div>\n	<div class=\"review-body\">ugly</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"review\">\n	<div class=\"review-head\">\n		<div class=\"reviewer-info\">\n			<div class=\"review-title-section\">\n				<h4 class=\"review-title\">Looks good but little susbtance without high cost</h4>\n				<div class=\"star-rating\">\n				<div class=\"wporg-ratings\" aria-label=\"1 de 5 estrellas\" data-title-template=\"%s de 5 estrellas\" data-rating=\"1\" style=\"color:#ffb900;\"><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span></div>				</div>\n			</div>\n			<p class=\"reviewer\">\n				Por <a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/rojasaj\"><img alt=\'\' src=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/8308dc48030c6c0efba4a271c87c34c0?s=16&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g\' srcset=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/8308dc48030c6c0efba4a271c87c34c0?s=32&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g 2x\' class=\'avatar avatar-16 photo\' height=\'16\' width=\'16\' /></a><a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/rojasaj\" class=\"reviewer-name\">rojasaj</a> el <span class=\"review-date\">March 12, 2019</span>			</p>\n		</div>\n	</div>\n	<div class=\"review-body\">Very limited in free. For some odd reason their calendar ends on Sunday (the first day of the week) and it was not readily apparent how to change that in settings.  </div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"review\">\n	<div class=\"review-head\">\n		<div class=\"reviewer-info\">\n			<div cl